":"1200–1274","1203–Male":"1203–Deceased","1205–Female":"1205–Deceased","1112–1208":"1112–1208","0001–Female":"0001–Deceased","1205":"1205","1203":"1203","1200":"1200","1112":"1112","1221":"1221","0001":"0001","1198":"1198","1274":"1274","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1208":"1208","Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France","Rodez, France":"Diocese of Rodez, France","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France","Rodez, Aveyron, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, France","France":"France","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Henry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["A perennially popular given name, of Continental Germanic origin, from <i>haim</i> ‘home’ + <i>rīc</i> ‘power, ruler’. It was an Old French name, adopted by the Normans and introduced by them to Britain. It has been borne by eight kings of England. Not until the 17th century did the form <i>Henry</i> (as opposed to   Harry  ) become the standard vernacular form, mainly under the influence of the Latin form <i>Henricus</i> and French <i>Henri</i>."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Rodez","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Catalan (<b>Rodés</b>): habitational name from any of several places called Rodés, mainly those in El Pallars and El Conflent districts, in northern Catalonia.","Catalan: variant of   Roda  , from Catalan <i>rodes</i>, plural of <i>roda</i> ‘wheel’.","English: variant of   Rhodes  . Compare   Rhode  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Rudes","meanings":["Americanized form of Croatian and Slovenian <b>Rudež</b>: nickname derived from <i>rud</i> ‘red, reddish’, or, alternatively, from <i>rud</i> ‘curly’ (standard Slovenian <i>rod</i>; compare   Rodes  ). In Croatia, the surname is also found in the form <b>Rudeš</b>."]},{"name":"Roda","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Rhoda ."]},{"name":"Rodas","meanings":["Variant spelling of   Rhoda ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Comte Henry de Rodez was born in 1174, in Diocese of Rodez, France, his father, Comte de Rodez, Benavent, Millau, Lodeve Hughes II de Rodez, was 62 and his mother, Bertrande d' Amaion, was 1173. He married Dame Algayette d' Escorallies de Benavent in 1198, in Rodez, Aveyron, France. They were the parents of at least 2 sons and 1 daughter. He died in 1221, in his hometown, at the age of 47."},"et":{"1174–1221":"1174–1221","1175–Female":"1175–Surnud","1200–1274":"1200–1274","1203–Male":"1203–Surnud","1205–Female":"1205–Surnud","1112–1208":"1112–1208","0001–Female":"0001–Surnud","1205":"1205","1203":"1203","1200":"1200","1112":"1112","1221":"1221","0001":"0001","1198":"1198","1274":"1274","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1208":"1208","Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, France":"Diocèse de Rodez, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Prantsusmaa","Rodez, Aveyron, France":"Rodez, Aveyron, Prantsusmaa","France":"Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1174–1221":"1174–1221","1175–Female":"1175–Kuollut","1200–1274":"1200–1274","1203–Male":"1203–Kuollut","1205–Female":"1205–Kuollut","1112–1208":"1112–1208","0001–Female":"0001–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1203":"1203","1200":"1200","1112":"1112","1221":"1221","0001":"0001","1198":"1198","1274":"1274","1175":"1175","1174":"1174","1172":"1172","1208":"1208","Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, France":"Millau, Aveyron, Midi-Pyrénées, Ranska","Rodez, France":"Diocèse de Rodez, R